company in the '40s.

00:33:43.571 --> 00:33:45.070
We've just been
waiting a long time.

00:33:47.661 --> 00:33:49.660
We decided selling home
improvement supplies was

00:33:49.660 --> 00:33:51.642
a good way to build capital.

00:33:51.642 --> 00:33:53.600
KELLY SANTIAGO: There's
a lot of responsibility

00:33:53.600 --> 00:33:57.490
to physical spaces and
people of all kinds.

00:33:57.490 --> 00:33:59.450
KYLE NEL: So without
waxing too philosophical,

00:33:59.450 --> 00:34:01.800
Lowe's mission is to help
people love where they live,

00:34:01.800 --> 00:34:05.010
and so the way that we
manifest that right now

00:34:05.010 --> 00:34:07.710
is through building these
stores all over North America.

00:34:07.710 --> 00:34:10.870
But clearly, that ambition
expands into the digital realm

00:34:10.870 --> 00:34:11.699
as well.

00:34:11.699 --> 00:34:15.949
And so when that's your goal,
the organization, hopefully,

00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:20.690
will modify itself in order
to help achieve whatever

00:34:20.690 --> 00:34:23.760
opportunities arise when you're
on this exponential path,

00:34:23.760 --> 00:34:25.350
especially on AR and VR.

00:34:25.350 --> 00:34:28.659
And so for us, when we started
down this a few years ago doing

00:34:28.659 --> 00:34:31.139
different platforms
and we did that

00:34:31.139 --> 00:34:34.600
with the intention of making
sure that the organization was

00:34:34.600 --> 00:34:37.850
malleable-- we didn't know it
was going to be called Tango

00:34:37.850 --> 00:34:38.940
or who was going to do it.

00:34:38.940 --> 00:34:42.639
But when it arrived, we
would be ready-ish for it.

00:34:42.639 --> 00:34:46.270
And ish is the key thing.

00:34:46.270 --> 00:34:49.800
And if you talk to any large
organization on the planet,

00:34:49.800 --> 00:34:53.110
not just a retailer, not just
a traditional business thing,

00:34:53.110 --> 00:34:56.060
they're all trying to
understand how to engage people

00:34:56.060 --> 00:34:57.740
in a more meaningful way.

00:34:57.740 --> 00:35:00.530
And what more meaningful way
than the most intuitive way,

00:35:00.530 --> 00:35:03.410
which right now I
think is clearly Tango?

00:35:03.410 --> 00:35:06.060
So once again, for
us, it's about showing

00:35:06.060 --> 00:35:08.810
what the promise could be
and the possibility could be

00:35:08.810 --> 00:35:11.874
and then trying to-- I
don't know if beat up

00:35:11.874 --> 00:35:13.540
is the right word,
but it's kind of what

00:35:13.540 --> 00:35:16.400
I do is beat up the
organization so that they will

00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:19.010
understand it and then jump on.

00:35:19.010 --> 00:35:23.760
But I will say that Lowe's has
gotten behind this in a big way

00:35:23.760 --> 00:35:26.967
because they see
the potential of it.

